observations.recommendation:
We reiterated our recommendation that the Municipal Mayor:
 require all the accountable officers to strictly comply with the provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 by immediately liquidating their cash advances and refund any unexpended balance; and
 instruct the Municipal Accountant to ensure that all cash advances are fully liquidated at the end of the year and to allow the granting of succeeding cash advance only when the previous one is fully liquidated;

We reiterated the recommendation that the
Municipal Mayor require:

a) all the accountable officers to liquidate immediately their cash advances;

b) the Municipal Treasurer to withhold the salaries or any amount due the accountable officers, to be applied to their accountabilities in case of their failure to liquidate their cash advances:;

c) the OIC — Municipal Accountant to:

e send demand letters to all accountable officers;

e allow the granting of succeeding cash advance only when the previous one is fully liquidated; and

e ensure that liquidation vouchers are submitted within the reglementary period.
